profile:
Absolute Home Services is a one stop shop for all of your home services. We currently specialize in:
 
1. Interior and Exterior Painting
2. Handyman Services
3. Lawn and Garden Maintenance
4. Landscaping
5. Interlock

 
Please contact us through email, website or phone call. The PING messaging service does not work well for communication purposes.
 
Customer satisfaction and retention is our primary focus. Therefore, we will do whatever it takes to ensure you are happy with our quality and service. Our goal is to have a customer for life! We want you to use us for all of our services, so we ensure you are happy after each service you use.
 
We service:
 
Mississauga, Oakville, Burlington, Hamilton, Milton, Toronto, Vaughan, Aurora, Newmarket, Barrie and Muskoka
 
We work on both commercial and residential projects.
 
Whether we are landscaping or painting, we have experienced people in each of their trades. Our painters take pride in what they do and are passionate providing high quality paint jobs. We have experts in interlock, lawn care and garden services who will give you the advice you need and a professional job.
 
Our service is what sets us a part from the rest. We have great people to provide great quality work, but we also have a goal to retain our customers for multiple services. In order to achieve this goal, we need to provide clear expectations, detailed quotes, communicate and deliver what we promise.

For 32 years, LawnSavers has focused on providing proven, organic-based solutions for Lawn Care & Tree Health Care. Our Fertilizing, Weed Control and Insect Pest Control Solutions are top notch. Naturally, this allows us to provide environmentally sustainable, healthy lawns & trees for a greener environment! 
 
We are a family-owned local Canadian company that's BIG ON SERVICE and taking care of people, including those team members that take care of you. We value old fashioned customer service, communication and partnership with our customers. We've grown a reputation of excellence through partnering with our clients. Deeply embedded in our culture, is that we always focus on great service, integrity, doing the right thing and real value. We are proud to be recognized as the 2022 "Best Lawn & Landscape Companies to work for" from Lawn & Landscape Magazine. 
 
We provide Natural & Organic Lawn care programs that include (better-than-golf course) Fertilizer, Effective Weed Control, Natural Insect Control & Pest Management. 
 
We specialize in lawn care services such as Weed control, weed removal, Lawn Renovation, No-Mess Liquid Aeration, PowerSeeding, OverSeeding, Topdressing & Compost Application, Mosquito Control, Perimeter Spider & Ant Control, Flea & Tick Control, Chinch Bug Control & Grub Control.
 
We are also a leader in Professional Christmas Lighting and Elegant Holiday Decorations!
 
Call or text us at 905-707-9994  416-707-9994 or 1-888-503-LAWN(5296) or visit https://lawnsavers.com to learn more and get a fast estimate customized for your property.

profile: Lawn Care Specialists who guarantee a healthy & green lawn Weed-A-Way is one of Canada's largest independent, family-owned and operated green lawn care companies. For over 4 decades our professional lawn care and weed control services have served customers in Mississauga, Brampton, Oakville, Burlington, Milton, Georgetown, and Caledon. Keeping a lawn vibrant, lush green, free of weeds, safe from insects and pests, is a shared responsibility between our professional staff and the home owner whose lawn we care for. A responsibility that we take very seriously and are deeply committed to. Download our Lawn Care Tips to stay on top of lawn maintenance. Now there’s a way to stop thinking "The grass is greener on the other side"! Weed-A-Way’s premium lawn care products and services will make your dream lawn a stunning reality. Here’s how: *As industry leaders and certified IPM (Integrated Pest Management) specialists, our lawn care programs utilize the most advanced turf management practices and products. *Our lawn amendment treatments as well as lawn care programs promote a vibrant landscape. *Depending upon weather conditions, we use a combination of Liquid and Granular fertilizers. Of course, if you prefer Granular, just let us know. *We guarantee results with our fertilizer and weed control programs. If after an application stubborn weed persists we'll come back and re-spray at no charge. Our services consist of the following programs and additional services: *Basic (Fertilizer & Weed Control) Lawn Care Program *Intermediate Organic Lawn Care Program *Advanced Lawn Care Program *Weed Control: FIESTA: A highly-recommended timely weed control which is composed of iron and is odourless, Fiesta kills the weeds but does not harm the lawn. It is applied by our highly qualified technicians throughout your season long program. Weeds compete with grass and plants for nutrients, water and sunlight. Broadleaf weeds are usually the greatest threat. If not dealt with quickly, they can destroy all your hard work. Effective weed control solutions from Weed-A-Way lawn services will ensure a healthy and vibrant lawn. We have extensive experience in dealing with various types of weeds like dandelion, broadleaf plantain, etc., and know how to deal with each one. *Core Aeration: The secret to a lush, green lawn is core aeration. Soil compacts over time and especially with traffic. Core aeration allows nutrients, water and oxygen to reach grass roots more easily. However, lawn aeration is more than just punching holes in the ground. You must have the proper equipment and be willing to set aside a couple of hours for aeration. It’s also important to know when your garden needs core aeration. Weed-A-Way’s lawn services take the trial and error out of grass treatments. We make sure that the grass is always green on your side of the fence. *Grub Treatment: Typically, grubs attack grass roots. A damaged root system results in a poor quality lawn with dirty, yellowish brown patches. Timely grub treatment from Weed-A-Way will avoid the huge expense of replacing your lawn as well as eliminate the threat of skunks and raccoons that feed on them. By using natural grub treatments like nematodes (naturally occurring microscopic worms) to destroy them and alfalfa treatments to stimulate roots, increase growth and drought resistance, our efficient lawn services will ensure a strong and healthy turf. *Crab Grass Control: Crabgrass forms thick clumps of light green leaves that are highly competitive with turf grasses. It turns brownish red in mid to late summer. Timely treatments are the most effective way to deal with crabgrass. Since this lawn problem germinates from seeds in spring it’s extremely important to apply the crabgrass control treatment before germination takes place. *Lime Treatment: In order to have healthy soil that supports grass growth, it is important to maintain the appropriate pH (acidity) balance. Using lime treatment is often the best solution. Although some lawn experts recommend lime treatment before starting a lawn, applications on mature turf also have several benefits. However, in order for your lime treatment to be effective, you must have knowledge of your soil’s pH levels. Our experienced lawn services will analyze a soil sample before applying lime treatment to your grass. We make sure we get it done right. *Surface Insect Control: Chinch bugs, sod webworms, cutworms and other surface insects usually strike in the summer. They are so small and usually buried in the lawn thatch; that’s why it so hard to spot them. Very often insect ridden grass looks dry and you might think it simply needs watering. Since your lawn is already stressed with the heat, drought-like conditions, weeds and traffic, the damage is greater. Weed-A-Way surface insect treatment means identifying your problems quickly and correctly, and then taking the appropriate control measures to eliminate the pests. *Overseeding and Core Aeration: Core aeration makes your overseeding efforts worthwhile. By unplugging the soil in a methodical way, you can remove thatch and reduce soil compaction as well as increase success of weed, surface insect and lime treatments. But a significant benefit of core aeration with regard to overseeding is that it allows the nutrients to reach the seeds and roots faster. Our expert lawn services can handle your overseeding and core aeration requirements to ensure proper effectiveness.

profile:
Frechette Lawncare is a family owned and operated business, servicing lawns in Toronto and surrounding areas for 50 years. We have an experienced team, on your lawns and in the office, that is ready to offer you lawn care that is effective and reliable. We are a responsible lawn care company, providing a healthy lawn that's healthy for you and your community.

Our season long program provides your lawn with frequent, light applications of perfect slow release fertilizer. This minimizes surge growth and eliminates any potential for leaching or runoff in your grass. This schedule also allows our technicians to monitor and address any problems as they arise throughout the season. Our fertilizers are custom blended, slow release, professional turf products made in Canada. They are a balanced combination of nutrients for your lawn. We fertilize your lawn the same way golf courses do theirs. Our fertilizers release nutrients gradually for a consistent feed all season long. The five applications include: spring, early summer, summer with kelp, late summer with kelp and fall fertilizers.
products:
We offer natural slow-release granular and liquid fertilizer. 

Fiesta Weed Control is a organic, iron based treatment that targets broad leaf weeds. 

The Grub Control is an organic treatment called Nematodes that target white grub and chinch bug. 

We also offer delivery of Ice Melter Reactor throughout the fall and winter season.
services: We offer a variety of lawn care services that will help your lawn looks its best. Our basic program is our Natural Fertilizers, which is 5 visits. We also offer natural weed control and grub control products. Additional services include aeration, over seeding and complete lawn restoration.

memberships: Landscape Ontario, National Association of Landscape Professionals

profile:
Geramon Irrigation has been in business over 2 years, in which we are very proud of. One of the reasons for our success is our Service Department, quick, professional, dependable, courteous service is our goal. We have a full time staff of technicians to fill all of your service needs, from the smallest adjustments to the redesign of your system due to landscape or other changes to your property.

We train each technician a minimum of four seasons before they are allowed to service systems on their own. Irrigation is a unique profession, each technician has to know all aspects of the industry, plumbing, electrical, system design, trouble shooting, general building construction, and so much more. To support our technicians in the field we have a full time office staff to answer your questions and schedule your service appointments.

profile:
Since the spring of 2000, Simple Solutions Landscaping has been offering quality services year-round in the North York neighborhoods of Armour Heights, Bathurst Manor, Clanton Park, Bayview Village, Newtonbrook, and Willowdale. We are dedicated to treating our clients with friendly and personalized customer service.

Brian Withey of Simple Solutions Landscaping is an established North York, and Toronto based landscaping company. They offer quality services year-round, with a focus on customer service. 

Since 2000, we've been helping people like you to maintain and enjoy the outside of your property.

Whether you are looking for general landscaping services or a company that can handle sodding, lawn aerating, grass cutting, hedge trimming, seeding, lawn dethachment or other property maintenance jobs, Simple Solutions has got you covered.

We improve the value of your property by caring for your yard. A new garden or walkway improves the curb appeal of your home. We create custom plans to suit your needs.

In the winter, we are on call 24/7 to remove snow from your drive and walkways with an easy fixed monthly bill. We use quality snow removal equipment to clear the path so you can feel safe and relaxed all winter long.

Simple Solutions is dedicated to ensuring you're satisfied with the job, we welcome your phone calls and questions. Call us today for help with your landscaping or snow removal needs!

profile:
Welcome to Forest Stumps

We offer Stump removal services for residential commercial, and Municipal projects throughout the GTA and Cottage country. Our stump removal is performed with a grinding process that is extremely neat and clean. We can remove any size stump in a safe manner. With the equipment we use at Forest Stump Grinding we are able to grind stumps as close as 8 inches from any existing sidewalks and driveways. Stumps can be not only an eyesore but a hazardous impediment to get around. For the safety of yourself and passers by, grinding down those exposed stumps is a absolute necessity. Give us a call or shoot us an email to learn more about what it is We can do to make your property safer and more beautiful.

Scott
Foreststumps40@gmail.com
416-559-6015
